channel.title: Help with server error?
channel.description: Hello, I am getting the following error when attempting to open a gate: [img]http://grab.by/grabs/8791f46d80ca1d4b800954c16f09e940.png[/img] The source I am using is [url=http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,391563.0.html]this[/url] Where are the handlers located..? (I know this is my second topic, my other one drowned somewhere back in the 2nd or 3rd page, i'm sorry)

item.title: Help with server error?
item.dc:creator: @Cooldude170 Cooldude170
item.description:
@Cooldude170 wrote:

[quote=“usman555, post:8, topic:366405”][quote author=Cooldude170 link=topic=462603.msg3385044#msg3385044 date=1288386784]

It’s not an error. It’s a debug message.

It means the option you chose isn’t handled - You clicked on that gate but the server doesn’t know what to do with that gate when you click it so it sends you a message.

Any way to handle them then?

Yea. Find where you’re getting the message - Probably from a default case in a switch statement then go from there.

I’m sort of new… :s
I’m using Bulby, what code and where would i place it to fix that?

Does it really matter? Why do you even want to fix it?

I kind of want to be able to use gates.
[/quote]Use a different gate. Because your server can’t handle this one.[/quote]
It seems to not be able to handle any, I had fixed castle wars (Finally) and the ladders and gates do not work.

Read full topic
